 :tx/rationale "PERFORMANCE ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS: braid status takes 8.5s with release binary at 33k datoms. Store load is only 0.7s (cache works). The 7.8s is pure computation. Root cause: REDUNDANT FULL-STORE SCANS. Status computes build_json AND build_status_projection, both of which independently call: compute_fitness (includes forward_scan → full datom iteration), methodology_gaps (full datom scan for crystallization), default_boundaries().evaluate_all (calls forward_scan + backward_scan → two full datom iterations each), derive_actions/compute_action_from_store (R(t) routing → PageRank over task graph). Total: build_json does ~4 full datom scans, build_status_projection does ~4 more. That's ~8 full iterations over 33k datoms. Each scan is O(33k). At 33k datoms, each scan takes ~0.5-1s. 8 scans = 4-8 seconds. MATCHES THE OBSERVED 7.8s. FIX: Compute-once-share-everywhere. Extract the expensive computations (fitness, boundaries, methodology_gaps, actions) into a StatusSnapshot struct computed once, then passed to both build_json and build_status_projection. This eliminates 4 of the 8 full scans immediately (50% speedup). Further: live_projections is called inside forward_scan, backward_scan, AND compute_fitness independently. Extract to a single call. forward_scan and backward_scan share impl_targets computation. Extract once. EXPECTED IMPROVEMENT: 8.5s → ~2s (4x speedup) via eliminating redundant computation. No algorithmic change needed — just caching intermediate results within a single status invocation. TRACES TO: INV-INTERFACE-008, ADR-STORE-005."
